OL,3,CTV-related anniversaries for 23 MAY
OL,4,CCHANNELS
OL,5,
OL,6,CG2005FBBC staff go on strike from
OL,7,Fmidnight on 23rd May 2005 for 24 hours.
OL,8,FThey were protesting at plans to cut
OL,9,F3,780 jobs and privatise parts of the
OL,10,FCorporation. The unions said the cuts
OL,11,Fwere the most damaging in BBC history.
OL,12,FThe Corporation said it regretted the
OL,13,Fdecision to take industrial action.
OL,14,
OL,15,FThe strike posed the most serious
OL,16,Fthreat to the BBC's programming
OL,17,Fschedule across all TV and radio
OL,18,Fnetworks in over a decade. BBC One and
OL,19,FBBC News 24 news output is disrupted:
OL,20,Fthe BBC News at One is presented by
OL,21,FSusan Osman; Stephen Cole presents both
OL,22,Fthe BBC News at Six and the BBC News at
OL,23,Sppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBOn This DayCClean FeedFNat TV
